cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the transmission of information and the performance analysis of different coding schemes. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper focuses on distributed computation and the impact of stragglers on the performance. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the transmission of information over a network and the impact of delays on the performance. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the control of a distributed system and the optimization of its performance. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the use of different coding schemes to optimize the performance of a distributed computation system.
